		<dc:creator><![CDATA[Mikayla Wyman]]></dc:creator>
		<pubDate>Tue, 16 Jun 2020 05:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
				<category><![CDATA[WordStream]]></category>
		<guid isPermaLink="false">https://www.wordstream.com/blog/ws/2020/06/16/goal-talk-episode-16/</guid>

					<description><![CDATA[<p>On this episode of the Goal Talk podcast, host Mikayla Wyman talks with SEO Special Gordon Donnelly about optimizing your site, keyword research tools, and more.</p>
<p>The post <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/ws/2020/06/16/goal-talk-episode">Goal Talk Podcast Episode 16: SEO Tips for Small Businesses</a> appeared first on <a href="https://www.wordstream.com">WordStream</a>.</p>
]]></description>
										<content:encoded><![CDATA[<section class="section">
<div class="section__inner section__inner--column_seperator">
<div class="column">
<div>
<p>On each episode of this season of the <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/goal-talk?utm_source=blog&amp;utm_medium=organic&amp;utm_content=">Goal Talk podcast,</a> I interview a marketing or management expert to bring small business owners and marketers the information they need to successfully <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/growth-academy">grow</a> their businesses.</p>
<p>So far on the podcast, we‚Äôve talked through many <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/ws/2020/01/07/best-marketing-strategies">marketing tactics</a> with our in-house experts, ranging from <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/ws/2020/02/18/goal-talk-podcast">creating your website</a> and getting your <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/ws/2020/03/03/goal-talk-episode-4">personas created</a> to specifics in <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/ws/2020/03/24/goal-talk-episode-7">paid ad auctions</a> and <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/ws/2020/04/28/goal-talk-episode-12">ad copywriting</a>, and many more in-between. So far, the majority of our conversations about search engine marketing have been about paid advertising tactics. And while <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/ppc">paid search marketing</a> is an extremely important part of a business‚Äôs marketing mix, we would be remiss if we didn‚Äôt spend some time discussing the organic side with search engine optimization.</p>
<div class="embedded-entity align-center" data-embed-button="images" data-entity-embed-display="view_mode:media.embed_image_narrow" data-entity-embed-display-settings="https://www.wordstream.com/goal-talk?utm_source=blog&amp;utm_medium=organic&amp;utm_content=SEO" data-entity-type="media" data-entity-uuid="6852ba1b-e04d-4d8b-8db5-89c5aa6f2b74" data-langcode="en">
<article>
<div><img decoding="async" src="https://www.wordstream.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/Goal-Talk-EpSEO-Square20SMALL_1.png" alt="Goal talk podcast episode 16 cover artwork - SEO for small businesses." width="800" height="800" /></div>
</article>
</div>
<p>Search engine optimization helps pages on your website rank well on search engines like Google and Bing so you can increase both the quality and quantity of your website traffic. SEO is a largely free tactic that will allow Google‚Äôs algorithm to intake your website content and rank it for a search query, based on the information on your website and the search itself. While in PPC you pay to have your link and headline show up at the top of the first page of the SERP, SEO is what powers the organic listings below the ads at the top of the page. So how do you <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/ws/2015/04/30/seo-basics">get started</a> in optimizing your website for SEO?</p>
<p>In this episode, WordStream&#8217;s in-house SEO manager <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/gordon-donnelly-2472">Gordon Donnelly</a> breaks down:</p>
<ul>
<li>The essential elements of <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/ws/2018/05/23/seo-for-startups">starting out in SEO</a>.</li>
<li>Tips for optimizing your site.</li>
<li><a href="https://www.wordstream.com/seo-software">Tools</a> for keyword research.</li>
<li>Resources to help keep you up to date with changes.</li>
</ul>
<p>And more! You can find this week‚Äôs episode on <a href="https://podcasts.apple.com/us/podcast/goal-talk-podcast/id1497955409">Apple Podcasts</a> and <a href="https://open.spotify.com/show/7BnP53IsIOkydFl1qPKD7E">Spotify</a>, as well as your favorite podcast app. Also, don‚Äôt forget to watch new episodes on our <a href="https://www.youtube.com/channel/UCrvBaHMLtSQ55IWAZiRQuQQ">YouTube channel</a>, and follow the podcast‚Äôs <a href="https://twitter.com/goaltalkpodcast">Twitter</a> account for episode releases, ask the hosts questions, and join in on the conversation.</p>
<div class="embedded-entity align-center" data-embed-button="videos" data-entity-embed-display="view_mode:media.embed_video" data-entity-type="media" data-entity-uuid="69ba4d0b-2279-4eb0-9aeb-a857c02e8222" data-langcode="en">
<article>
