<p>It‚Äôs been two full weeks since we‚Äôve had an episode of the <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/goal-talk?utm_source=blog&amp;utm_medium=organic&amp;utm_content=">Goal Talk podcast</a>, and while we‚Äôre embracing our updated bi-weekly episode release schedule, we missed releasing an episode last week! So it only felt right to bring a guest <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/ws/2020/04/21/goal-talk-episode-11">back onto the podcast</a> this week to bring an update on the state of digital marketing during COVID-19 for advertisers.</p>
<h2>This week: Current updates on COVID-19 marketing tips, performance data, and account reactivation</h2>
<p>Last time we had <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/mark-irvine-42">Mark</a> on the podcast, we discussed the preliminary data around how the social effects of social distancing and mandatory business practice modifications have impacted digital marketing for advertisers. That <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/ws/2020/04/21/goal-talk-episode-11">episode</a>¬†was released about a month ago as we were navigating the first few weeks of the majority of the effects of the pandemic worldwide. In the episode, we discussed how search trends and patterns are shifting, some options for small business assistance from the government, and the data around how the mandated changes have impacted the <a href="https://www.wordstream.com/blog/ws/2020/03/18/covid-19-google-ads-data">PPC results</a> for multiple industries.</p>
<div class="embedded-entity align-center" data-embed-button="images" data-entity-embed-display="view_mode:media.embed_image_narrow" data-entity-embed-display-settings="https://www.wordstream.com/goal-talk?utm_source=blog&amp;utm_medium=organic&amp;utm_content=" data-entity-type="media" data-entity-uuid="4f42fa09-67da-41f4-8cfe-497e6122101b" data-langcode="en">
